cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CL 

The paper proposes a method for learning disentangled image representations without manual labeling or data domain knowledge. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The use of autoencoder architecture and training objectives also suggests that the paper may belong to the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and neural networks (cs.NE) sub-categories. Finally, the paper demonstrates the effectiveness of the proposed approach on image classification and retrieval tasks, which suggests that it may also belong to the natural language processing (cs.CL) sub-category.
